# @lanza/site ships CODE only; the `files` allowlist in package.json is the source
# of truth for what's included (it enumerates the platform public/ subdirs, so tenant
# media and generated files are never listed). This file exists solely so npm does
# NOT fall back to .gitignore for packing — which would drop the prebuilt admin SPA
# under public/admin (gitignored in the repo, produced by the prepack build).
